    Allows a common feature extractor to be applied to multi-dimensional data. The dimension of the data expected is configurable but is expected to be perfectly interleaved. So for 3-d XYZ data the data is expected as 
     xyzxyz...xyz
    Feature extract proceeds as follows:
    1. De-interleave the data
    2. apply the feature extractor separately to each dimension of data
    3. concatenate the resulting features into a single array.
